==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Columbite
<hw>Co*lum"bite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>colombite</ets>. See <er>Columbium</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of a black color, submetallic luster, and high specific
specific gravity. It is a niobate (or columbate) of iron and manganese,
containing tantalate of iron; -- first found in New England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

